column19: I did not get to use Lounge Buddy. I would like a refund of my $88. No where on your site do you say you need a boarding pass to go to Level 6/7 at Shanghai Terminal 1. The United counter was closed and wasn't going to open again till 8 a.m. the next morning. Without a boarding pass they wouldn't let me go up to Lounge Buddy. I had a reservation for 12 hours which I paid $88. I slept in the airport lobby and after I received my boarding pass at 8:15 a.m. I went to LoungeBuddy and talked toMun Gurung at the desk and she said I should ask for a refund as I would only be able to use the lounge for 30 minutes. Please refund my money. I really think the LoungeBuddy is a good service when you can access it. Please put in your website that you need to have a boarding pass to access yourself to that level. I finally connected to wifi and presented the email I had with the barcode, after a lot of disapproving and tutting I was permitted to enter, without any apology or anything.  I was quite disappointed as I was a paying customer and I didn't feel I was treated with a lot of respect and zero friendliness.  This is quite off putting for future layovers.  Maybe staff need to be made more aware of different methods of booking into a lounge and basic customer service skills.

Fyi I was traveling with my elderly Mother, and the lounge was on the second floor (no lift) and we bringing several luggage. So we finally arrived on the correct lounge, the guy was rejecting us and keep telling us the voucher from LoungeBuddy is not worth it. So disappointing. We have to bring our luggage and I have to hold my Mother to go to first floor (although the guy know that they have working lift behind him, and he was not allowing us to use it. I guess, we still a bit lucking, there was a lady show how difficult my Mom going down, and she mentioned that I can use the lift. We come back after half way down and almost used the lift. And she asked what's going on, I told her that we have voucher from LoungeBuddy, and finally she checked on her computer. She finally let us in. Ridiculous!!! We cannot even take shower there, because no one open the bathroom door. What kind of lounge is it???
